latestIgtvVideos.title: A Walk Down Memory Lane I
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Major shoutout to my heart and soul sister @revati75 for making this edit back when I was graduating college. It features my classmates from acting school - or as we called ourselves, Dumbledore‘s Army. There’s snippets from many of our classes and performances, a class photo from our first Halloween in drama school when we all dressed as our teachers until the final graduating class photo. So many memories compressed into this short clip. Oh what I would give to be back in the room with these guys, learning about the craft and being my most authentic self. The three years I spent at @theatrelasalle set me up to be the actor and person I am today. I would be nothing without the love and guidance of my classmates and teachers. So thank you @edithpodesta @thespismaker @boots_and_sunglasses @stefanosrassios for being the greatest mentors I could’ve ever asked for, for dealing with my bullshit, my ups and downs and for pushing me to realise my potential, for being cool role model adults I could look up to only to grow up and realise myself that it’s not as easy as y’all made it look. 
And to my Dumbledorians... what do I even say? I carry you with me in my heart every single day. You lot mean the world to me and I would never have been able to love myself if not for your love! I can’t wait for all of us to meet again and get crayyy on the dance floor, as only we can. Till then I wish you all more life, the great work continues ❤️
@morwennamaclean @spandyandrei @chanelarielchan @lian.sutton @benhew @chngxinxuan @shananigansssssssss @francesxoxo @dominiquedemarco @axelshmermel 
#throwback #nostalgia

latestPosts.caption:
Within a span of four short earth days - so many moments of depth and truth, from a godhbharai to a funeral to spoken fest to a chaat party…
time spent with friends, celebrating life, grieving and loss, celebrating the easy love of soul friends and family, soaking up artistic truths, and marinating in the inescapable truth that life is a wild wild ride and God’s grace is unparalleled 💕💫

How have the last few days been? Life can truly change any second. Take time to just be. To just love. To just sit in it all and soak it all in.
